== Buttery Bulgur ==

Pour the @water for the bulgur{220%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, stir in half the @Chicken Stock Paste{20%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @Bulgur Wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%min}.

Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{12-15%mins} or until ready to serve.

== Lamb Pasanda Curry ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Lamb Mince{200%g} and onion. Cook until browned and softened, ~{5-6%mins}.

Use #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the lamb fries, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Stir the garlic and @Pasanda Style Seasoning{1%sachet} into the lamb mince. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Once the mince is browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

Stir in the remaining chicken stock paste, @Tomato Passata{1%carton} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once thickened, stir the @Mango Chutney{40%g}, @Peas{120%g} and @Butter{10%g} into the curry and heat until the peas are piping hot and the butter is melted, ~{1%min}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== Assembly ==

When the bulgur is cooked, fluff up the grains with a #fork{}.

Share the bulgur between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the lamb pasanda curry.

Finish by drizzling over the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g}. Enjoy!